Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane says perceptions that she's shielding President Jacob Zuma are unjustified. CAPE TOWN - Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane says perceptions that she's shielding President Jacob Zuma are unjustified and that her office will hold him accountable. Mkhwebane spoke to journalists on the side-lines of a 16 Days of Activism for No Violence against Women and Children event in Khayelitsha on Thursday.There have been claims she's compromised and protecting Zuma. Mkhwebane denies this: Why would I shield the president? If the president has committed any conduct or there s a service failure, he will be investigated. I m here to defend and implement the Constitution. She says her office's job is to defend the Constitution: The Constitution provides for the right of every South African and my role is to protect the public and not an individual. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)